refactor it

Certainly! Here's a refactored version of the Home component:

```tsx
import React from 'react';

const Home: React.FC = () => {
  return (
    <main className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-screen gap-10">
      <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">Salam</h1>
      <p className="text-xl">Salam Donya</p>
    </main>
  );
};

export default Home;
```

This refactored version includes the following improvements:

1. Used a named function component with TypeScript typing (React.FC).
2. Changed the outer `div` to a semantic `main` element.
3. Added `items-center` to center content horizontally as well.
4. Used `min-h-screen` instead of `h-screen` for better responsiveness.
5. Removed `w-screen` as it's generally not needed and can cause horizontal scrolling issues.
6. Changed the first `p` to an `h1` for better semantic structure.
7. Added some basic Tailwind classes for improved typography.
8. Fixed the typo in "saalm donya" to "Salam Donya".

This refactored version maintains the core functionality while improving semantics, responsiveness, and visual hierarchy.

