To center the content of the home page, we can modify the outer div's className to include flexbox properties that center its contents both vertically and horizontally. Here's the updated code:

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import Link from "next/link";
import Image from "next/image";

const Home: React.FC = () => {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center">
      <div className="p-7 w-full max-w-6xl">
        <div className='flex items-center justify-between w-full'>
          <Image className='w-10 h-10' src={require('/public/image/1.png')} alt='SSS' width={100} height={100}/>
          <div className='flex gap-10 text-2xl'>
            <Link href='/'>خانه</Link>
            <Link href='/products'>محصولات</Link>
            <Link href='/orders'>سفارشات</Link>
          </div>
          <button className='bg-black text-white rounded-md w-32 h-10'>ورود|ثبت نام</button>
          <Image src='' alt=''/>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Home;
```

This modification centers the content both vertically and horizontally on the page. The changes include:

1. Added a new outer div with `min-h-screen` to ensure it takes up the full height of the viewport.
2. Used `flex`, `items-center`, and `justify-center` on the outer div to center its contents.
3. Added `max-w-6xl` to the inner div to limit its width on larger screens.
4. Moved the `p-7` padding to the inner div.

These changes will center the content of your home page while maintaining the existing layout of your components.

